SIMPLE: tuneless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tuneless
<hw>Tune"less</hw> <pr>(t⟦umac⟧n"l⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Without tune; inharmonious; unmusical.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧
Thy <xex>tuneless</xex> serenade.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Cowley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How often have I led thy sportive choir,⟦br⟧
With <qex>tuneless</qex> pipe, beside the murmuring Loire!</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not employed in making music; <as>as,
<ex>tuneless</ex> harps</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not expressed in music or poetry; unsung.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tuner</ent>⟦br⟧
